Cuba Send Doctors to Hurricane-Hit Nicaragua
HAVANA , November 21 ( Xinhua ) -- A team of Cuban medical doctors left for Nicaragua on Saturday to help victims of Hurricane Mitch in the remote areas of that country .
Official sources said that five more medical teams will follow at the request of the Nicaraguan authorities .
The Cuban government announced last Wednesday that it was ready to send a total of 2,000 physicians free of charge to Central American nations devastated by Mitch in the last week of October .
Several Cuban medical teams are now helping the relief in Honduras , which suffered the worst during Mitch 's rampage of the region .
The other two teams are working in Guatemala .
